# ingestion-service

Polls cybersecurity RSS feeds, deduplicates articles by URL hash, embeds them,
and upserts the results into Postgres + pgvector. Communicates with the rest of
the system only through Postgres and the job queue — never by importing another
service.

## Status

The service runs two concurrent tasks:

1. **RSS poller** — fetches 6 curated cybersecurity RSS feeds every
   `POLLING_INTERVAL_SECONDS` (default 900s / 15 min), normalizes URLs,
   deduplicates by `url_hash` against `processed_jobs`, and enqueues
   `article.discovered` jobs onto the Redis BullMQ queue.
2. **BullMQ worker** — consumes `article.discovered` jobs, generates a
   384-dim embedding (`sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) from the
   article title + snippet, and upserts into the `articles` table with
   pgvector (`ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE`).

Embedding failures set `embedding_status=failed` so the row can be retried
later. Feed timeouts and parse errors are logged and skipped — they never
crash the worker.

## Run

```bash
docker compose up ingestion-service
```

## How it works

```
RSS feeds → poller.py → article.discovered queue → worker.py → handler.py
                                                              ↓
                                          embeddings.py (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)
                                                              ↓
                                               db.py (pgvector upsert)
```

## Redis port configuration

Redis runs on port **6379** inside the Docker network and is exposed to the
host on **6380** (configurable via `REDIS_PORT`). This avoids conflicts with a
locally-installed Redis instance.

| Scenario | Connection string |
|---|---|
| Inside Docker (default in `worker.py`) | `redis://redis:6379/0` |
| Local development (outside Docker) | `redis://localhost:6380/0` (set in `.env`) |

The Python default in `worker.py` is `redis://redis:6379/0` because the service
runs inside Docker. When running locally, set `REDIS_URL` in your `.env` to
`redis://localhost:6380/0`.

## Environment

| Variable | Default | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `DATABASE_URL` | `postgresql://b0bot:b0bot@postgres:5432/b0bot` | Postgres connection |
| `REDIS_URL` | `redis://redis:6379/0` | BullMQ queue |
| `ARTICLE_DISCOVERED_QUEUE` | `article-discovered` | Queue name |
| `POLLING_INTERVAL_SECONDS` | `900` | RSS polling interval (15 min) |
| `RSS_FEED_TIMEOUT` | `10` | Timeout per feed in seconds |
| `EMBEDDING_MODEL` | `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` | HuggingFace embedding model |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | `INFO` | Logging level |

## Test the pipeline

```bash
# Start the stack
docker compose up -d

# Check worker logs (poller + consumer)
docker compose logs -f ingestion-service

# Verify articles in postgres
docker compose exec postgres psql -U b0bot -d b0bot \
  -c "SELECT title, url_hash, embedding_status FROM articles ORDER BY ingested_at DESC LIMIT 10;"

# Verify idempotency markers
docker compose exec postgres psql -U b0bot -d b0bot \
  -c "SELECT * FROM processed_jobs ORDER BY processed_at DESC LIMIT 10;"

# Check queue length in Redis
redis-cli -p 6380 LLEN article-discovered

# Hybrid vector search (cosine similarity)
docker compose exec postgres psql -U b0bot -d b0bot \
  -c "SELECT title, embedding <-> (SELECT embedding FROM articles WHERE embedding IS NOT NULL LIMIT 1) AS distance
      FROM articles
      WHERE embedding IS NOT NULL
      ORDER BY distance
      LIMIT 5;"